
This is the Perl distribution Module-Pluggable-Loader.

## Installation

Module-Pluggable-Loader installation is straightforward.
If your CPAN shell is set up, you should just be able to do

    % cpan Module::Pluggable::Loader

Download it, unpack it, then build it as per the usual:

    % perl Makefile.PL
    % make && make test

Then install it:

    % make install

## Documentation

Module-Pluggable-Loader documentation is available as in POD.
So you can do:

    % perldoc Module::Pluggable::Loader

to read the documentation with your favorite pager.
